This paper deals with the security of software countermeasures against cache attacks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves reasoning about memory accesses and hardware architecture, which suggests that it could be classified under computer architecture (cs.AR) or systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing software code, which could place it under software engineering (cs.SE) or programming languages (cs.PL).
